{"title":"Road to Philly Bike Expo 2021: Tom La Marche Breaks and Makes Bikes","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/27/tom-la-marche-breaks-and-makes-bikes-philly-bike-expo-interview/","date":1635357880000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"a yellow Tom La Marche bike in a wooded environment\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-274377\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>From riding with the Specialized team to TIG welding his own frames – Tom La Marche’s career has been nothing if not varied. Tom was driven to make frames out of a desire to ride something he created. We caught up with Tom in advance of the Philly Bike Expo, where he’ll be debuting a mountain bike frame he’s been cooking up. He’s also working on a foldable bike!</p><p>Please enjoy this interview with Tom La Marche.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183513/la-marche-pbe-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183513/la-marche-pbe-8.jpg\" alt=\"a La Marche frame against a white background\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183513/la-marche-pbe-8.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183513/la-marche-pbe-8-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183513/la-marche-pbe-8-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183513/la-marche-pbe-8-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183513/la-marche-pbe-8-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183513/la-marche-pbe-8-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: What’s your name, your bike brand, and where are you based?</strong></p><p><strong>Tom La Marche:</strong> Tom La Marche, Philadelphia, PA. I started apprenticing frame building in 2015, so 6 years.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183717/la-marche-pbe-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183717/la-marche-pbe-4.jpg\" alt=\"a collection of bike frame materials \" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183717/la-marche-pbe-4.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183717/la-marche-pbe-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183717/la-marche-pbe-4-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183717/la-marche-pbe-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183717/la-marche-pbe-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183717/la-marche-pbe-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: What’s your preferred frame material and building technique?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Tom:</strong> Steel with a mixture of TIG welding and fillet brazing.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183623/la-marche-pbe-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183623/la-marche-pbe-7.jpg\" alt=\"Tom La Marche TIG welding\" width=\"1067\" height=\"1600\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183623/la-marche-pbe-7.jpg 1067w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183623/la-marche-pbe-7-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183623/la-marche-pbe-7-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183623/la-marche-pbe-7-80x120.jpg 80w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183623/la-marche-pbe-7-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183623/la-marche-pbe-7-1024x1536.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1067px) 100vw, 1067px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: What sets your bikes apart from other custom builders?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Tom:</strong> Branding, semi-production, no-frills, lots of riding experience.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183756/la-marche-pbe-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183756/la-marche-pbe-3.jpg\" alt=\"a collection of bike frames of different colors against a white background\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1068\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183756/la-marche-pbe-3.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183756/la-marche-pbe-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183756/la-marche-pbe-3-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183756/la-marche-pbe-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183756/la-marche-pbe-3-768x513.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183756/la-marche-pbe-3-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: How did you get into this? Who inspired you to get started making bikes?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Tom:</strong> Years of breaking frames, being unsatisfied with frame designs, and ultimately just wanting to ride something I created. I think some of the first examples of frame building that inspired me to make bikes were Brooklyn Machine Works, Ted James Designs, and Squarebuilt.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1.jpg\" alt=\"a yellow Tom La Marche bike in a wooded environment\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183855/la-marche-pbe-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: Who inspires you now?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Tom:</strong> Anyone who breaks outside of the norm. The people making their own tooling and frame parts really get me horny. Some of my favorites are: Tonic Fabrications, Tommi, BTR, Swarf, Hunter, WHTHOUS, Foes, Chapman Cycles, Frances Cycles, PechTregon, Moulton, Thursday Bikes, S&amp;M, Ted James, Bike Friday, Clandestine, Starling Cycles, Eeder Metal, Falconer, and Inglis/ Retrotech.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183941/la-marche-pbe-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183941/la-marche-pbe-2.jpg\" alt=\"tools and frame parts in a workshop\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183941/la-marche-pbe-2.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183941/la-marche-pbe-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183941/la-marche-pbe-2-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183941/la-marche-pbe-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183941/la-marche-pbe-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11183941/la-marche-pbe-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: How was Covid era for you? Good, bad, about the same? How did it change your business and business model, if at all?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Tom:</strong> I moved into a new workshop at the begging of the pandemic which kept me plenty busy. Luckily I was able to work alone and not interact with many other people. This is my first year as an actual business, so tough to say.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184035/la-marche-pbe-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184035/la-marche-pbe-6.jpg\" alt=\"a wider shot of the Tom La Marche workshop\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184035/la-marche-pbe-6.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184035/la-marche-pbe-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184035/la-marche-pbe-6-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184035/la-marche-pbe-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184035/la-marche-pbe-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184035/la-marche-pbe-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: What’s the most interesting bike you’ve built over the past year?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Tom: </strong>I’m currently working on a folding travel bike that compacts into a manageable size. It’s single speed, uses some BMX parts, and is very simple. I got sick of stressing over all of the ever-changing standards and wanted to build something that brought things back to basics. Riding and traveling are the two best things to me. Why not make a bike that suits that lifestyle?&nbsp; It’s fun to build things to your own standards and not have to worry about squeezing tires, chainring, and cranks into a 1 mm clearance zone. Going with a BMX crank allows an adjustable chain line and will be the heart of the folding mechanism.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184311/la-marche-pbe-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184311/la-marche-pbe-9.jpg\" alt=\"a Tom La Marche bike against a white background\" width=\"1067\" height=\"1600\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184311/la-marche-pbe-9.jpg 1067w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184311/la-marche-pbe-9-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184311/la-marche-pbe-9-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184311/la-marche-pbe-9-80x120.jpg 80w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184311/la-marche-pbe-9-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184311/la-marche-pbe-9-1024x1536.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1067px) 100vw, 1067px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: What are you bringing to Philly Bike Expo this year? Any teasers or sneak peeks?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Tom: </strong>Hopefully two do-it-all/gravel bikes and a mountain bike frame. You’ll have to wait and see!</p><p>It’s been a ton of work to design the bike and dial in all the details so I am very excited to bring it to the public and start producing them.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184345/la-marche-pbe-10.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184345/la-marche-pbe-10.jpg\" alt=\"Tom La Marche working in his shop\" width=\"1068\" height=\"1600\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184345/la-marche-pbe-10.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184345/la-marche-pbe-10-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184345/la-marche-pbe-10-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184345/la-marche-pbe-10-80x120.jpg 80w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184345/la-marche-pbe-10-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/11184345/la-marche-pbe-10-1025x1536.jpg 1025w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1068px) 100vw, 1068px\"></a></p><p><strong>Bikerumor.com: If you had to do a multi-day bikepacking adventure with anyone else in the cycling industry, dead or alive, who would it be and why?&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Tom:</strong> Hm, maybe the Wright brothers? Would be cool to see what kind of contraption they could come up with for bikepacking.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/lamarchebikeco/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>lamarchebikeco</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Andrew Marshall","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ee00e9fd3b41362bbda7c22a4a5f348ae70fddfed1e7bfd9887ffb37c68853af","category":"Cycling"}